<br>
I can answer that concern, and while we both are just spectulating at this time, we can always dream.<br>
<br>
Thing is this is being treated as a ability (listed as such) and not a spell, but that fact only does not exclude this as it is listed as a spell or effect, but there is no recast timer listed in the spell file. There is only a cast timer and a recovery time listed in this particular spell. Spell recovery is not related to spell fizzle recovery, this timer is the time it takes for all spells to 'ungrey' after casting a spell. Normally when we cast a spell and it fizzles you notice that all spells including the spell we was casting ungreys automatically, no delay. Spell recovery refers to the time it takes to cast ANOTHER spell overall, not the time it takes to recast the same spell. And spell recast time refers to the time it takes for THAT spell to ungrey. Now, if there was no recast time listed then the spell would be bound by the spell recovery time instead. And so based on this knowledge is where I determinded the numbers. But neither of use knows FOR SURE what that POP AA skill will do until we are able to use it, only then will we both know for sure.<br>
<br>
